<Slide>
	<h2>Quand soudain... 😨</h2>
</Slide>

<Slide>
	<div class="r-stack">
		<img
			src="/images/iphone-keynote/1.webp"
			alt="Steve Jobs at the first iphone keynote"
		/>
		<img
			class="fragment"
			src="/images/iphone-keynote/2.webp"
			alt="Steve Jobs at the first iphone keynote"
		/>
		<img
			class="fragment"
			src="/images/iphone-keynote/3.webp"
			alt="Steve Jobs at the first iphone keynote"
		/>
		<img
			class="fragment"
			src="/images/iphone-keynote/4.webp"
			alt="Steve Jobs at the first iphone keynote"
		/>
		<img
			class="fragment"
			src="/images/iphone-keynote/5.webp"
			alt="Steve Jobs at the first iphone keynote"
		/>
	</div>
</Slide>

<Slide>
	<h2>Le design web adaptif 💡</h2>
	<ul>
		<li class="fragment">Détection du user-agent lors de la requête serveur</li>
		<li class="fragment">Une page différente est servie en fonction du user-agent (mobile, desktop...)</li>
		<li class="fragment">En 3G, nécessité de dégrader les médias servis sur la page</li>
	</ul>
</Slide>

<Slide>
	<h2>Un héritage du design physique</h2>
	<img
		src="/images/intro/physical-design.webp"
	 	alt="a design on different physical supports"
	/>
</Slide>

<Slide>
	<h2>Une conception vite limitée...</h2>
	<ul>
		<li class="fragment">Arrivée de smartphones d'autres marques, multiplication des devices... et des tailles d'écrans !</li>
		<li class="fragment">Annonce de l'iPad en 2010</li>
		<li class="fragment r-stack">
			<img src="/images/intro/ipad-keynote.webp" alt="Steve Jobs holding an iPad" />
			<img class="fragment" src="/images/intro/ipad-keynote-google.webp" alt="Steve Jobs holding an iPad" />
		</li>
		<li class="fragment">Déploiement de la 4g à partir de 2012</li>
	</ul>
</Slide>

<Slide>
	<h2>Une autre approche 🧠</h2>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="fragment">
			<img src="/images/intro/ethan-marcotte-portrait.webp" alt="portrait of Ethan Marcotte" />
			<span>Ethan Marcotte</span>
		</div>
		<img class="fragment" src="/images/intro/responsive-web-design-article.webp" alt="screenshot of the responsive web design article" />
	</div>
</Slide>

<Slide>
	<h2>La philosophie du design responsif 🌊</h2>
	<div class="r-stack">
		<div class="fragment fade-in-then-out">
			<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/cJMwBwFj5nQ?si=VSZSrlROeUxHaVIy&amp;controls=0&cc_lang_pref=fr&cc_load_policy=1" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>
		<ul>
			<li class="fragment">Renoncer au contrôle des media physiques</li>
			<li class="fragment">Créer une page unique mais fluide, qui soit acceptable à toutes les tailles</li>
			<li class="fragment">Accepter l'imperfection</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</Slide>

<Slide>
	<h2>Un parallèle avec l'architecture 📐</h2>
	<img src="/images/intro/the-shed.webp" alt="the shed" />
</Slide>

<Slide>
	<img src="/images/intro/layout-methods-timeline.webp" alt="a timeline of web layout methods" />
	<a target="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AMPKmh98XLY">Jen Simmons - Designing Intrinsic Layouts (2018)</a>
</Slide>

<Slide>
	<h2>Une multitude de techniques 🤯</h2>
	<ul>
		<li class="fragment">multicol</li>
		<li class="fragment">floats</li>
		<li class="fragment">media queries</li>
		<li class="fragment">unités relatives</li>
		<li class="fragment">flexbox</li>
		<li class="fragment">grid</li>
		<li class="fragment">container queries</li>
	</ul>
</Slide>

<style>
	img {
		max-height: 600px;

		li > & {
			max-height: 200px;
		}

		& + span {
			display: block;
			font-size: 0.8em;
		}
	}

	li:has(img) {
		list-style: none;
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
	}

	.row {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;

		img {
			max-height: 360px;
		}
	}

	a {
		display: block;
	}
</style>
